UK ' S FTSE TURNS LOWER AFTER DATA , RATE FEARS WEIGH . UK shares had turned lower again ahead of the U . S . opening on Wednesday after higher than expected U . S . price data followed a batch of strong domestic data , putting interest rate concerns back in the spotlight . The FTSE 100 index was off 10 . 2 points at 4 , 346 . 6 by 1350 GMT . Advancing stocks outweighed losers by roughly five - to - four . UK stocks extended losses after U . S . February CPI figures showed a rise of 0 . 3 percent , compared with forecasts of 0 . 2 percent . The Dow was expected to open lower on worries over a possible early rate hike on March 25 , the date of the next FOMC meeting in the U . S . 
